Settings

Business Information

Your business name appears in the header and will be used in calendar invites and emails sent to your clients.

📋 Session Types

Define the types of sessions your studio offers (1–5 types). These names are used across the entire system — calendar, client rates, income reporting, and online booking.

📅 Scheduling Options

🏠 Rooms / Equipment

Enable room or equipment tracking to add a dropdown to calendar bookings. Rooms or equipment cannot be double-booked — only one session can use a given room or piece of equipment at the same time.

Leave blank any slots you don't need. At least one name is required.

🌐 Online Client Booking

Allow clients to book their own appointments through a shareable link. Most studios manage bookings themselves — only enable this if you want clients to self-book.

🔗

Set each staff member's working hours. Clients will only see times when their chosen staff member is available. Staff not listed below won't appear on the booking page.

No staff members found. Add staff in Settings → User Management first.

💳 Payment Settings

Connect Stripe or PayPal to charge clients directly from session bookings. Invoicing for e-Transfer and cash/prepaid tracking are always available.

🌍
💜
Stripe — Accept Credit & Debit Cards

Charge client cards directly. Funds go to your Stripe account.

Find your API keys at dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys. Use test keys (pk_test_ / sk_test_) to try it out first. Standard fees: 2.9% + $0.30 per transaction.

🅿️
PayPal — Accept PayPal, Cards & More

Clients pay via PayPal popup — cards, PayPal balance, or bank.

Get your Client ID from developer.paypal.com → Dashboard → Apps. Use sandbox credentials to test. Standard PayPal fees apply.

📄 Invoicing (e-Transfer)

Always available. Send invoices for clients who pay via e-Transfer.

💵 Cash / Prepaid

Always available. Record cash payments or mark prepaid packages.

📧 All payment methods automatically generate an email receipt to the client.

Calendar & Email Integrations

Connect your calendar and email accounts to automatically create events when booking sessions.

📅 Google Calendar Integration

Connect your Google account to automatically create calendar events and send invites to clients.

✓ Connected

📧 Microsoft Outlook / Microsoft 365 Integration

Connect your Microsoft account to access Outlook Calendar and Email for automated scheduling and client communications.

✓ Connected to Microsoft Outlook

What you get:

  • Automatically create Outlook calendar events for sessions
  • Send appointment reminders via Outlook email
  • Invite clients to sessions with calendar events
  • Works with personal Outlook and Microsoft 365 business accounts

💰 Practitioner Pay Rates

Set how much each practitioner earns per session type. This is used to calculate payroll costs, gross margin, and profitability on the Income dashboard.
